{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1522,"text":"So, I'm going to start off with kind of the buzzkill a little bit."},{"time":5500,"text":"Forty-two million people"},{"time":7631,"text":"were displaced by natural disasters in 2010."},{"time":10741,"text":"Now, there was nothing particularly special about 2010,"},{"time":13812,"text":"because, on average, 31 and a half million people"},{"time":17108,"text":"are displaced by natural disasters every single year."},{"time":20211,"text":"Now, usually when people hear statistics or stats like that,"},{"time":22759,"text":"you start thinking about places like Haiti or other kind of"},{"time":25553,"text":"exotic or maybe even impoverished areas, but it happens"},{"time":28973,"text":"right here in the United States every single year."},{"time":32096,"text":"Last year alone, 99 federally declared disasters"},{"time":35111,"text":"were on file with FEMA,"},{"time":37357,"text":"from Joplin, Missouri, and Tuscaloosa, Alabama,"},{"time":40548,"text":"to the Central Texas wildfires that just happened recently."},{"time":44939,"text":"Now, how does the most powerful country in the world"},{"time":47004,"text":"handle these displaced people?"},{"time":49103,"text":"They cram them onto cots, put all your personal belongings"},{"time":51532,"text":"in a plastic garbage bag, stick it underneath,"},{"time":53700,"text":"and put you on the floor of an entire sports arena,"},{"time":56715,"text":"or a gymnasium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60226,"text":"So obviously there's a massive housing gap,"},{"time":63288,"text":"and this really upset me, because academia tells you"},{"time":66196,"text":"after a major disaster, there's typically about"},{"time":68485,"text":"an 18-month time frame to -- we kinda recover,"},{"time":71824,"text":"start the recovery process,"},{"time":73401,"text":"but what most people don't realize is that on average"},{"time":75766,"text":"it takes 45 to 60 days or more"},{"time":78830,"text":"for the infamous FEMA trailers to even begin to show up."},{"time":81692,"text":"Before that time, people are left to their own devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85310,"text":"So I became obsessed with trying to figure out a way"},{"time":88686,"text":"to actually fill this gap."},{"time":90836,"text":"This actually became my creative obsession."},{"time":93390,"text":"I put aside all my freelance work after hours and started"},{"time":96095,"text":"just focusing particularly on this problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101837,"text":"So I started sketching."},{"time":103196,"text":"Two days after Katrina, I started sketching and sketching"},{"time":105220,"text":"and trying to brainstorm up ideas or solutions for this,"},{"time":107068,"text":"and as things started to congeal or ideas started to form,"},{"time":110226,"text":"I started sketching digitally on the computer,"},{"time":112452,"text":"but it was an obsession, so I couldn't just stop there."},{"time":115921,"text":"I started experimenting, making models,"},{"time":118060,"text":"talking to experts in the field, taking their feedback,"},{"time":120838,"text":"and refining, and I kept on refining and refining"},{"time":123749,"text":"for nights and weekends for over five years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126805,"text":"Now, my obsession ended up driving me to create"},{"time":130290,"text":"full-size prototypes in my own backyard — (Laughter) —"},{"time":132575,"text":"and actually spending my own personal savings on"},{"time":134941,"text":"everything from tooling to patents"},{"time":137190,"text":"and a variety of other costs,"},{"time":139806,"text":"but in the end I ended up with this modular housing system"},{"time":142670,"text":"that can react to any situation or disaster."},{"time":145332,"text":"It can be put up in any environment,"},{"time":148431,"text":"from an asphalt parking lot to pastures or fields,"},{"time":152374,"text":"because it doesn't require any special setup"},{"time":154377,"text":"or specialty tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156559,"text":"Now, at the foundation and kind of the core"},{"time":158279,"text":"of this whole system is the Exo Housing Unit,"},{"time":161213,"text":"which is just the individual shelter module."},{"time":163646,"text":"And though it's light, light enough that you can actually"},{"time":165378,"text":"lift it by hand and move it around,"},{"time":167534,"text":"and it actually sleeps four people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171237,"text":"And you can arrange these things as kind of more"},{"time":173901,"text":"for encampments and more of a city grid type layout,"},{"time":176676,"text":"or you can circle the wagons, essentially,"},{"time":178571,"text":"and form these circular pods out of them,"},{"time":180582,"text":"which give you this semi-private communal area"},{"time":183038,"text":"for people to actually spill out into so they're not actually"},{"time":185807,"text":"trapped inside these units."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187906,"text":"Now this fundamentally changes"},{"time":190331,"text":"the way we respond to disasters,"},{"time":192489,"text":"because gone are the horrid conditions"},{"time":194467,"text":"inside a sports arena or a gymnasium, where people"},{"time":197192,"text":"are crammed on these cots inside."},{"time":199204,"text":"Now we have instant neighborhoods outside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204791,"text":"So the Exo is designed to be simply, basically"},{"time":207766,"text":"like a coffee cup. They can actually stack together"},{"time":210008,"text":"so we get extremely efficient transportation"},{"time":212933,"text":"and storage out of them."},{"time":215184,"text":"In fact, 15 Exos can fit on a single semi truck by itself."},{"time":219820,"text":"This means the Exo can actually be transported and set up"},{"time":222994,"text":"faster than any other housing option available today."},{"time":227978,"text":"But I'm obsessive, so I couldn't just stop there,"},{"time":229967,"text":"so I actually started modifying the bunks where you could"},{"time":231856,"text":"actually slide out the bunks and slide in desks or shelving,"},{"time":234164,"text":"so the same unit can now be used"},{"time":235676,"text":"for an office or storage location."},{"time":238901,"text":"The doors can actually swap out, so you can actually put on"},{"time":242619,"text":"a rigid panel with a window unit in it for climate control,"},{"time":245488,"text":"or a connector module that would allow you to actually"},{"time":247954,"text":"connect multiple units together, which gives you"},{"time":250339,"text":"larger and kind of compartmentalized living spaces,"},{"time":254005,"text":"so now this same kit of parts, this same unit"},{"time":256317,"text":"can actually serve as a living room, bedroom or bathroom,"},{"time":260960,"text":"or an office, a living space and secure storage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267067,"text":"Sounds like a great idea, but how do you make it real?"},{"time":270134,"text":"So the first idea I had, initially, was just"},{"time":272138,"text":"to go the federal and state governments and go,"},{"time":273994,"text":"\"Here, take it, for free.\""},{"time":276657,"text":"But I was quickly told that, \"Boy, our government"},{"time":278640,"text":"doesn't really work like that.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":280898,"text":"Okay. Okay. So maybe I would start a nonprofit"},{"time":284883,"text":"to kind of help consult and get this idea going"},{"time":287726,"text":"along with the government, but then I was told,"},{"time":289829,"text":"\"Son, our government looks to private sector"},{"time":292304,"text":"for things like this.\""},{"time":293901,"text":"Okay. So maybe I would take this whole idea and go"},{"time":296891,"text":"to private corporations that would have this mutually shared"},{"time":299311,"text":"benefit to it, but I was quickly told by some corporations"},{"time":302214,"text":"that my personal passion project was not a brand fit"},{"time":306495,"text":"because they didn't want their logos stamped"},{"time":309073,"text":"across the ghettos of Haiti."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311497,"text":"Now, I wasn't just obsessed. I was outraged. (Laughter.)"},{"time":317433,"text":"So I decided, kind of told myself,"},{"time":321850,"text":"\"Oh yeah? Watch this. I'll do it myself.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":327725,"text":"Now, this quickly, my day job sent me to work out of"},{"time":329905,"text":"our Milan office for a few months, so I was like,"},{"time":333059,"text":"what will I do? So I actually scheduled sleep on my calendar,"},{"time":335796,"text":"and spent the 8-hour time difference on conference calls"},{"time":338996,"text":"with material suppliers, manufacturers and potential customers."},{"time":343016,"text":"And we found through this whole process, we found"},{"time":344470,"text":"this great little manufacturer in Virginia,"},{"time":346844,"text":"and if his body language is any indication,"},{"time":348997,"text":"that's the owner — (Laughter) — of what it's like"},{"time":351076,"text":"for a manufacturer to work directly with a designer,"},{"time":353169,"text":"you've got to see what happens here. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356372,"text":"But G.S. Industries was fantastic."},{"time":358628,"text":"They actually built three prototypes for us by hand."},{"time":363008,"text":"So now we have prototypes that can show that four people"},{"time":366155,"text":"can actually sleep securely and much more comfortably"},{"time":368571,"text":"than a tent could ever provide."},{"time":373068,"text":"And they actually shipped them here to Texas for us."},{"time":374818,"text":"Now, a funny thing started happening."},{"time":376271,"text":"Other people started to believe in what we were doing,"},{"time":378739,"text":"and actually offered us hangar space, donated hangar"},{"time":380656,"text":"space to us. And then the Georgetown Airport Authority"},{"time":382940,"text":"was bent over backwards to help us with anything we needed."},{"time":387046,"text":"So now we had a hangar space to work in,"},{"time":388707,"text":"and prototypes to demo with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391789,"text":"So in one year, we've negotiated manufacturing agreements,"},{"time":395356,"text":"been awarded one patent, filed our second patent,"},{"time":398017,"text":"talked to multiple people, demoed this to FEMA"},{"time":400700,"text":"and its consultants to rave reviews,"},{"time":402948,"text":"and then started talking to some other people who requested"},{"time":405131,"text":"information, this little group called the United Nations."},{"time":407622,"text":"And on top of that, now we have"},{"time":409727,"text":"a whole plethora of other individuals that have come up"},{"time":412371,"text":"and started to talk to us from doing it for mining camps,"},{"time":415862,"text":"mobile youth hostels, right down to the World Cup"},{"time":418294,"text":"and the Olympics."},{"time":420879,"text":"So, in closing, on this whole thing here"},{"time":427971,"text":"is hopefully very soon we will not have to"},{"time":432627,"text":"respond to these painful phone calls that we get"},{"time":434548,"text":"after disasters where we don't really have anything"},{"time":436544,"text":"to sell or give you yet."},{"time":438932,"text":"Hopefully very soon we will be there,"},{"time":441364,"text":"because we are destined,"},{"time":443571,"text":"obsessed with making it real."},{"time":447677,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}